<body>
    <h1>Rapid Recovery Information Hub</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p local-id=3D"4947d24636b2"><a class=3D"external-link" data-card-a=
ppearance=3D"inline" href=3D"https://mfc.sharepoint.com/:f:/r/sites/ets-jap=
an/Program%20Delivery/Lapu-Lapu/02_Technical_SOP/Rapid_Recovery?csf=3D1&amp=
;web=3D1&amp;e=3DOgbs1U" local-id=3D"226e808aab33" rel=3D"nofollow">https:/=
/mfc.sharepoint.com/:f:/r/sites/ets-japan/Program%20Delivery/Lapu-Lapu/02_T=
echnical_SOP/Rapid_Recovery?csf=3D1&amp;web=3D1&amp;e=3DOgbs1U</a></p>
<p local-id=3D"a42390b87aab"><strong>Purpose</strong>: This page is the aut=
horitative, Confluence-ready hub for <strong>Rapid Recovery Plans (RRP)</st=
rong> for <strong>Ingenium</strong> and other <strong>MLJ Internal Applicat=
ions</strong> supported by the Prod Support (PS) Team.</p>
<p local-id=3D"69a8f7c19d11">It explains <strong>when Rapid Recovery is inv=
oked</strong>, <strong>how it is executed</strong>, and <strong>how RRPs mu=
st be documented and registered</strong>. Ingenium is the reference impleme=
ntation; all other MLJ internal apps should follow the same standard.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"9541bd77-d961-4999-be79-c6043f1cd1e0">
<h2 local-id=3D"eaf2912d6107" id=3D"RapidRecoveryInformationHub-1.Scope">1.=
 Scope</h2>
<p local-id=3D"26fcf9ab18db"><strong>In scope</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"0a8c0e32-fdef-43a6-b5e2-8ce1d82b5b37">
<li local-id=3D"7cb0a09f-9798-4a1f-98a9-f2708d975926">
<p local-id=3D"74e073986ba4">Ingenium =E2=80=93 App =E2=80=93 Japan (refere=
nce / first standard)</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"71fe99d3-a680-42f2-8735-2fddb0b1ab0a">
<p local-id=3D"e6dbcd764b51">All other MLJ Internal Applications supported =
by Prod Support</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"6c31d02d47b8"><strong>Out of scope</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"5486cc7c-77a6-447b-ad02-17b0fee9f17d">
<li local-id=3D"2aabc447-4c70-477b-abfb-3e141c3e4c83">
<p local-id=3D"f75cfa48075b">Non-MLJ applications not supported by PS</p></=
li>
<li local-id=3D"468ca000-52b4-46f5-9834-10d346053d69">
<p local-id=3D"67967051aeb4">Standard incidents where Rapid Recovery criter=
ia are not met</p></li>
</ul>
<hr local-id=3D"1bbbf174-931d-48bf-8d88-46fd7f07c203">
<h2 local-id=3D"a9e6d54e92ee" id=3D"RapidRecoveryInformationHub-2.WhatisRap=
idRecovery?">2. What is Rapid Recovery?</h2>
<p local-id=3D"cf6ab697f9f9">Rapid Recovery is a <strong>pre-approved, step=
-driven recovery process</strong> used during <strong>Severity 1 or Severit=
y 2</strong> incidents to restore service as quickly as possible using <str=
ong>known, rehearsed recovery actions</strong>.</p>
<p local-id=3D"b768a6c2d622">Key characteristics:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"8214374b-2f7d-49ba-8619-c186c7129d26">
<li local-id=3D"f4a6174d-27ac-4f59-be20-a01a53b5556e">
<p local-id=3D"360a32106418">Executed only under defined <strong>Sev1 / Sev=
2</strong> conditions</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"89273948-9a16-4170-8e92-968bf9b0be1b">
<p local-id=3D"db3fc6a76645"><strong>All numbered steps must be executed</s=
trong> in sequence</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"42c77dfd-da26-46b5-bf1b-a20635d86b86">
<p local-id=3D"2225f9bc9a15">Explicit communications when the <strong>Rapid=
 Recovery process is invoked</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"ae6eb5cf-82d9-4cd3-9e95-56797497b08f">
<p local-id=3D"966553001b46">Focused on <strong>service restoration</strong=
>, not root-cause resolution</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"8503f12d-5dc2-4b0d-8ade-dfd450458a23">
<p local-id=3D"314bf12458dc">Followed by <strong>post-incident change docum=
entation</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<blockquote local-id=3D"51f26b82-933b-4e4a-bad2-c99c6a0e8aaa">
<p local-id=3D"ea58c25c70d0">If recovery actions deviate from the defined s=
teps, standard Incident / Change processes apply instead.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr local-id=3D"3020256a-4e8c-4c6a-a121-c20643f6c198">
<h2 local-id=3D"62ba874ff9b2" id=3D"RapidRecoveryInformationHub-3.WhentoInv=
okeRapidRecovery(Ingeniumexample)">3. When to Invoke Rapid Recovery (Ingeni=
um example)</h2>
<p local-id=3D"b454f3ac2b87">Rapid Recovery may be invoked for Ingenium whe=
n service impact is broad or time=E2=80=91critical, including but not limit=
ed to:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"df1cdc92-15ae-4021-b317-adae02ae13d3">
<li local-id=3D"74063e58-ba6a-47bd-b3db-515d538f097d">
<p local-id=3D"29dfc34f6d53">System-wide unavailability or severe degradati=
on</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"b351f509-d5c4-4d97-93cd-0e8fb585e4b9">
<p local-id=3D"e6e477180701">DB or data-related incidents requiring restore=
/recovery</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1a9302e9-7ceb-4bd6-b0a8-c7ef95dfc5fe">
<p local-id=3D"bf127d73e017">Batch or job failures blocking business proces=
sing</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"a467dd4c-8ff2-484a-8267-974af9fc608a">
<p local-id=3D"5951d13469e6">Configuration or deployment failures requiring=
 rollback</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"0f796848-0873-4cce-882d-448539a9e9c3">
<p local-id=3D"64ebd5594886">External dependency or vendor-related failures=
</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"331643ef-631b-4efe-8236-3b15a8a125b4">
<p local-id=3D"9085aebabdf0">Access, credential, or certificate failures</p=
></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"c7046f52fcf6">Rapid Recovery is <strong>not</strong> used fo=
r minor, localized, or non-production issues.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"e5f71839-af04-44ac-982d-b7a0f0bdd871">
<h2 local-id=3D"a3b1196f5bcb" id=3D"RapidRecoveryInformationHub-4.RapidReco=
veryExecution=E2=80=93StandardFlow">4. Rapid Recovery Execution =E2=80=93 S=
tandard Flow</h2>
<p local-id=3D"875dca4015f7">This execution backbone applies to <strong>Ing=
enium and all MLJ internal apps</strong>.</p>
<ol start=3D"1" local-id=3D"bbcd82b7-954d-457e-b6fa-0fe0508c2656">
<li local-id=3D"d954f6a3-f49a-449b-a796-7de4ae355568">
<p local-id=3D"eb15832c4c0b"><strong>Escalate to Severity 1 / 2</strong></p=
>
<ul local-id=3D"18260c7d-902c-43da-bdb9-a4ea7f6e7fca">
<li local-id=3D"0d32c3ff-4b54-45d5-adfe-77a59c4f04a0">
<p local-id=3D"a91b54b15f5b">Incident raised and correctly categorized</p><=
/li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"de571a08-f9bc-4351-bc5e-45dfd9bd1f26">
<p local-id=3D"8426e11829b1"><strong>Engage required support teams</strong>=
</p>
<ul local-id=3D"6f5149a6-86f9-4364-9844-78fc3a47b8fe">
<li local-id=3D"07d031ff-04a6-4707-bc62-b247112dc083">
<p local-id=3D"9d1b384b0959">Prod Support</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"287f32ac-c625-4a2d-b70c-873d26cfb908">
<p local-id=3D"ac4ad99e5766">Infrastructure</p></li>
<li local-id=3D"1deb5c1f-eb17-4f84-a2c6-791544615d1f">
<p local-id=3D"1cb0dcb8fe85">Vendors / third parties (as applicable)</p></l=
i>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"bb0c11d8-f2b7-4217-899e-beaff03947de">
<p local-id=3D"0d06f48407b8"><strong>Initial communication sent</strong></p=
>
<ul local-id=3D"0f9725ee-6f60-4556-9090-15fce5681d56">
<li local-id=3D"68fce49e-4da6-4f7e-a3c9-451ccce3856b">
<p local-id=3D"cb150566a5eb">Scope and impact communicated once known</p></=
li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"0a40738b-be2d-451b-899e-836a83723e1d">
<p local-id=3D"94a70f9d38d0"><strong>Open conference bridge</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"31cf3dc7-d2d3-477a-94c9-98e1045df55f">
<li local-id=3D"e7bc007b-cd5c-40d7-9ea8-6ab0d07baf87">
<p local-id=3D"b6e9be68cec5">All required technical and coordination roles =
join</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"5a70cce4-e854-4ff6-af1b-c18902b57683">
<p local-id=3D"0a3113a6a573"><strong>Assess system state &amp; decide recov=
ery action</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"a81d426e-ef7e-406a-a5a7-0a486ca79467">
<li local-id=3D"9f8b2c06-72ab-4a76-83b0-259701a31197">
<p local-id=3D"8eaec45dbab3">Rolling restart / hard restart / restore / rol=
lback</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"d6280966-b1b2-451d-8d64-cfb56196da07">
<p local-id=3D"c974b712a29c"><strong>Invoke Rapid Recovery (explicit comms)=
</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"e23d9dca-58d8-497c-b987-e82813c60a9d">
<li local-id=3D"256bcb25-26ca-4398-985c-008fc0f2fba1">
<p local-id=3D"e1a1fa29503c">Notification states that <em>Rapid Recovery is=
 being invoked</em></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"b8e41837-46c0-4b66-841b-649f34dbf0ee">
<p local-id=3D"51f7b8fc42e3"><strong>Execute recovery steps</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"c6253892-83bf-43f9-a73b-d7e4ce776309">
<li local-id=3D"d4b9ea45-41e9-4041-88b7-8a856dd3a69a">
<p local-id=3D"2b3c9c294de2">Follow the RRP runbook exactly</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"b2fcf4c2-09dd-463c-b87a-aff19e93436a">
<p local-id=3D"7ad34a3bcc41"><strong>Validate service restoration</strong><=
/p>
<ul local-id=3D"ffa8d24e-5c98-4d68-b249-93cac8408b73">
<li local-id=3D"e4f47580-53c2-44f8-b249-618086ab0b99">
<p local-id=3D"357ab899d691">Basic functional and technical checks</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"1ebd128c-5515-4819-985b-b92ae4fcfe5f">
<p local-id=3D"f24a835fed6b"><strong>Confirm recovery time</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"335958b9-5486-4d7d-833c-8fa9e7b9c8e6">
<li local-id=3D"077fafb6-7973-441c-92b5-ce7cefba5bec">
<p local-id=3D"adf4454c9080">Update incident record</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li local-id=3D"9b82e521-2988-4d0e-bc70-3b0971d72821">
<p local-id=3D"119a8c0b5e97"><strong>Send recovery notification</strong></p=
></li>
<li local-id=3D"43a8fea8-207e-4d38-ae26-4efea07dc619">
<p local-id=3D"53893d31dd72"><strong>Close bridge</strong></p></li>
<li local-id=3D"e89a3b71-4eee-4357-ba13-0aa2a2c3c838">
<p local-id=3D"2529ad4a004f"><strong>Post-incident activity</strong></p>
<ul local-id=3D"d9fdebf4-f104-4663-b580-150677288696">
<li local-id=3D"aae7ed35-8304-4249-ac3c-445f71dbc892">
<p local-id=3D"10472da9d9a7">Create or update Change record (as required)</=
p></li>
</ul></li>
</ol>
<hr local-id=3D"3d2f7bb7-697a-4246-9b6b-e57d262f758c">
<h2 local-id=3D"bbda57869dfd" id=3D"RapidRecoveryInformationHub-5.Ingenium=
=E2=80=93ReferenceRRPCoverage">5. Ingenium =E2=80=93 Reference RRP Coverage=
</h2>
<p local-id=3D"41b469d48fe4">Ingenium RRPs must be <strong>runbook-style</s=
trong> and cover the following recovery scenarios:</p>
<ul local-id=3D"89f4eebd-184c-4986-a3fc-e71f994972da">
<li local-id=3D"0200b289-7b28-43c7-9ed8-78ad674860e8">
<p local-id=3D"529548eb5751"><strong>Data incidents</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"6d516516ed67">Backup, restore, reconciliation (DB2 full + in=
cremental restores)</p>
<ul local-id=3D"58d3a6ef-d70c-4124-9b2c-12e7bb94f67c">
<li local-id=3D"0f77f202-9703-4bb7-a42f-c7884dd23476">
<p local-id=3D"31e0ed3e339a"><strong>Batch / job failures</strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"89c669879b51">Controlled restarts, reruns, checkpoint-based =
recovery</p>
<ul local-id=3D"97483534-7bb9-48a7-8490-c21bdf15d1b3">
<li local-id=3D"42e2ea24-0f7f-4a66-b758-e90426885e0a">
<p local-id=3D"76a5868dbd08"><strong>Configuration / deployment failures</s=
trong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"2ff4ebd10318">Rollback to last known good state</p>
<ul local-id=3D"89bd0661-74a4-4521-8da9-4ee3c474dcc1">
<li local-id=3D"f957a001-ee67-419e-bd0e-b016a30cbf88">
<p local-id=3D"69799daf413b"><strong>Integration &amp; dependency failures<=
/strong></p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"bcf9dfa0debf">Vendor escalation, mitigation, or workaround</=
p>
<ul local-id=3D"bb6b4135-761d-4d7f-b6be-64aed8b55a72">
<li local-id=3D"4bb0a13c-6388-497b-9bcd-2d24751e9c53">
<p local-id=3D"e64ef7bc1063"><strong>Access / credential issues</strong></p=
></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"68db79ff6d7e">Break-glass access and remediation steps</p>
<ul local-id=3D"e88874ce-310d-4f1d-b1dd-4bb9aa2dc084">
<li local-id=3D"e20786f1-f6b6-4656-848a-368538f31d2f">
<p local-id=3D"509ad3cb747b"><strong>Release-related instability</strong></=
p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ff4893ea9442">Partial rollback or stabilization actions</p>
<p local-id=3D"360383817603">These scenarios form the baseline for other ML=
J internal applications.</p>
<hr local-id=3D"63af85a2-2cb4-4f7d-bcbc-2a6a5a04c70d">
<h2 local-id=3D"9c8bb27fcbd8" id=3D"RapidRecoveryInformationHub-6.WhatanRRP=
DocumentMustContain">6. What an RRP Document Must Contain</h2>
<p local-id=3D"92ce287ff4c4">Each Rapid Recovery Plan must include:</p>
<h3 local-id=3D"a964c2f1e6b7" id=3D"RapidRecoveryInformationHub-6.1CoreReco=
veryTable">6.1 Core Recovery Table</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"e403c070-6607-43d0-a520-d0c=
a11d2fb7a" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr data-local-id=3D"9400d157-0d6e-411e-a57c-16b20d8dd6bc">
<td data-local-id=3D"7e80bebb-b9f1-4d37-a3e7-8b675e856415" class=3D"conflue=
nceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ad09b77803e0">Step</p></td>
